# Contributing to {{ project_name }}

Thanks for contributing! This project holds a high bar for quality and security — the gates make
it easy to meet.

## Before you start

Read **[`CLAUDE.md`](CLAUDE.md)** (the working contract), **[`docs/CODING_STANDARDS.md`](docs/CODING_STANDARDS.md)**,
and **[`docs/DEVELOPER_GUIDE.md`](docs/DEVELOPER_GUIDE.md)**.

## Workflow

1. Branch off `develop`: `feat/*`, `fix/*`, `refactor/*`, `docs/*`.
2. Make one logical change. Keep files ≤ 400 lines, routers thin, everything typed and tested.
3. Run the gate locally: `make check && make dod-check`.
4. Complete the **Definition of Done** ([`CLAUDE.md`](CLAUDE.md) §2): update `docs/PLAN.md`,
   `docs/LESSONS.md`, `docs/architecture/current-state.md`, an ADR if the decision is new, and
   `CHANGELOG.md`.
5. Open a PR (the template lists the checklist). CI must be green; a maintainer reviews.

## Commit messages

**Conventional Commits:** `type(scope): summary` — `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `docs`, `test`,
`chore`, `security`, `perf`.

## Security & secrets

Never commit secrets or keys. Report vulnerabilities privately — see
[`.github/SECURITY.md`](.github/SECURITY.md).

